			<Question qid="0003841-1" qtype="information">What is (are) Taking medicines to treat tuberculosis ?</Question>
			<Answer>Tuberculosis  (TB) is a contagious bacterial infection that mainly involves the lungs, but may spread to other organs. The goal of treatment is to cure the infection with medicines that fight the TB bacteria.</Answer>
